properties.headline: Flood Advisory issued February 16 at 9:26AM CST until February 17 at 9:25PM CST by NWS Nashville TN
properties.description:
...The National Weather Service in Nashville has issued a Flood Advisory for the
following rivers in Middle Tennessee...

Duck River Near Hurricane Mills affecting Humphreys County

. Waters remain high at the Duck River near Hurricane Mills. The river will continue
to fall and be below action stage by Tuesday morning.

The National Weather Service in Nashville has issued a
* Flood Advisory for
The Duck River Near Hurricane Mills
* At 9 AM Sunday the stage was 19.7 feet.
* Action stage is 16.0 feet.
* Flood stage is 20.0 feet.
* The river will continue to fall to near 17.3 feet by tomorrow morning.
* At 16.0 feet...Water begins to inundate agricultural land and other low lying
areas along the river including access points from Bucksnort to Taylortown,
Cedar Grove, and to Bakerville Rd.
properties.instruction:
Stay tuned to NOAA weather radio or other local media for further information
from the National Weather Service.
